Little Calculator in C

A simple calculator that supports basic mathematical operations. The project is written in C and uses pointers for passing parameters between functions.

Features
    Addition (+)
    Subtraction (-)
    Multiplication (*)
    Division (/)
    Modulo (%)

Installation and Usage
    Clone the repository or download the calc.c file.
    Compile the program:
        gcc -o calc calc.c -lm
    Run the calculator:
        ./calc
    Follow the prompts to enter two numbers and select a mathematical operation.
Notes
    If division by zero is attempted, an error message will be shown.
    The modulo operation also handles division by zero and shows an error message.
